Enhancement: Allow backing up directly from an S3 bucket or an rclone remote

The `backup` command now accepts an S3 location or an rclone remote as its
source, for example `restic backup s3:s3.example.com/mybucket/prefix` or
`restic backup rclone:myremote:bucket/path`. Data is read straight from the
remote service, without mounting it first, and stored with restic's usual
deduplication, encryption and snapshot handling.
Credentials for an S3 source are read from `$RESTIC_SOURCE_ACCESS_KEY_ID`
and `$RESTIC_SOURCE_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY`, falling back to the default
AWS/MinIO credential chain; rclone sources use the regular rclone
configuration.

Unchanged objects are detected via size and modification time and skipped
without any data transfer, like unchanged files in a local backup.

